channel.title: [PI]-317-Female Problem, Prayer changes after relogging, Clicking Problem.Help!
channel.description:
Hello guys,
My PI 317 Server has some problems foudn by my mates. I have taken some screenshots to explain it more.
So the first problem is with the Female Character. She doesnt wear anything good. Here some screenshots of it: [img]http://www.upload.ee/image/3188562/MeisjeSOL.png[/img] [img]http://www.upload.ee/image/3188565/meisjeVLS.png[/img] [img]http://www.upload.ee/image/3188566/ProbleemMeisjeWhip.png[/img]
Next problem is my Prayer, when you changed your prayer to Curses and you relog its back to Normal prayers.
Then a problem found by my mate and it is Switching, switching is like good now the speed but it sometimes does not register the clicks. Like when u change from Melee set to Magic set fast it sometimes doesnt register it. Also my friends call it Drag-Scape.. They say it means that if you switch gear sometimes it drags it to a diffrent place, also wanna know how to fix that.
Then the last problem is PMaul, its 1 handed. i know its easy to fix but i have no clue where i fix it =P.
[img]http://www.upload.ee/image/3188560/1hPMAULENmeid.png[/img]
Oh yeah and at my client it has the Remember me? Button, but it doesnt work. How do i make this work? [img]http://www.upload.ee/image/3188559/332.png[/img]
I would really appreciate if someone could give me the help i really need.
Remco.

item.title: [PI]-317-Female Problem, Prayer changes after relogging, Clicking Problem.Help!
item.dc:creator: @sk8rdude461 sk8rdude461
item.description:
@sk8rdude461 wrote:

[quote=“Project Fantastico, post:2, topic:511675”]It has to do with the char files in the cache.

or deadlocks[/quote]
Dude. Fucking really?

No. It’s your ints. They’re the wrong wield models for females.

Sup22211:

Change the female models, i cant help you with this because on PI i dont know how.

Hey look something that knows it.

It’s client sided in ItemDef.java (can be ItemDef_2)
Here’s an example of the “raptor” cestplate (recolored BCP):

		itemDef.anInt165 = 66619;
		itemDef.anInt200 = 67877;

anInt165 = Male weilding
anInt200 = Female Weilding
